    "subtask_body": "Final verification and any last improvements.\n\nTSP tour [0,11,10,6,5,1,15,3,18,2,16,12,4,13,9,8,17,7,14,19] computed \u2248452.6. Let me try one more 2-opt: the segment 2\u219216\u219212\u21924 involves long edges 2\u219216(68.1) and 12\u21924(34.1). Try reversing to connect differently. Also try or-opt: move city 4 elsewhere. 4(3,59) is far left. Nearest to 4: 9(31,48)=30.1, 13(27,52)=25.0, 12(1,93)=34.1, 8(47,60)=44.1. Currently 12\u21924\u219213. Try inserting 4 between 9 and 8: [0,11,10,6,5,1,15,3,18,2,16,12,13,9,4,8,17,7,14,19]. 12\u219213: sqrt(676+1681)=48.6, 9\u21924: 30.1, 4\u21928: 44.1, vs 12\u21924: 34.1, 4\u219213: 25.0, 9\u21928: 20.0. New: 48.6+30.1+44.1=122.8 vs old: 34.1+25.0+20.0=79.1. Much worse.\n\nTry or-opt moving 17 (9,17): currently 8\u219217\u21927. 8(47,60)\u219217(9,17): 57.4, 17\u21927(20,14): 11.4, 7\u219214(35,23): 17.5. If remove 17: 8\u21927: sqrt(729+2116)=53.4, save 57.4+11.4-53.4=15.4, but need to insert 17 elsewhere. Best insertion: between 7(20,14) and 14(35,23): 7\u219217: 11.4, 17\u219214: sqrt(676+36)=26.7, vs 7\u219214: 17.5. Cost: 11.4+26.7-17.5=20.6. Net: -15.4+20.6=+5.2. Worse. Between 14(35,23) and 19(56,16): 14\u219217: 26.7, 17\u219219: sqrt(2209+1)=47.0, vs 14\u219219: 22.1. Cost: 26.7+47.0-22.1=51.6. Worse.\n\nSteiner at 61 is confirmed optimal for this approach. CJS at 164 baseline. TSP at ~452.6 is good improvement from 554.4.",
